Attach a 3 GB hard disk to Windows VM. 
Create 2 partitions. First one of 2 GB and second one of 1 GB
Format both the partitions using NTFS.
Create some files in both the partitions. ( atleast 4 files and type something in these files)
Now format both the partitions .....Use diskmgmt.msc
Now delete both the partitions. 
Detach the 3 GB hard disk from the Windows VM and attach it to forensics VM.
Create a directory using sudo /recovered 
Using testdisk and photorec recover the files in /recovered directory.
